@bellapescia Agree most windows and doors should have catalog files with standard sizes and configurations pre-made, we will need to do some office training to teach people not to load every size in the catalog.
I was thinking it might be helpful if we had all the catalog files saved as excell files and have a macro to save it out as a CSV file, and rename it to a .txt
Ideally a one button solution. What do you think?

@ian_james : you link some files in to the template for each discipline... once you create a new file the links are "Not Found" but that doesn't matter... what you can do is pre-set views for coordination that have the links turned on or off... etc...
When you get real files from the consultant you just Reload From and the real file replaces the dummy link and all of the views set up should already work...

@ian_james to publish the RTC article by Arron Maller

@paulwintour: regarding saving a project version of the SP file.
that's exactly how we do it in Brisbane, I agree this needs to be the national workflow.
it also stops the national SP file filling up with Project specific SPs.
for example we have some defense projects that have about 30 parameters that are only used on that project (client requirements)

